2026-04-30T13:05:23.5618947Z             "body": "## Summary\nThis PR enhances the web UI with client-side domain history tracking, improves navigation consistency across pages, and adds root-only user deletion functionality to the auth system.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n**Frontend Improvements:**\n- Added client-side domain history using localStorage, persisted to a `<datalist>` for native autocomplete suggestions (max 50 domains)\n- Refactored navigation UI across all pages (index.html, tokens.html, config.html) with consistent styling and layout:\n  - Introduced `.nav` class with flexbox layout and flex-wrap for responsive design\n  - Added `.current` class to highlight the active page\n  - Standardized \"who\" and \"sign out\" link styling\n  - Updated navigation to show \"Signed in as {username}\" and conditionally hide sign-out when auth is disabled\n- Improved textarea styling in config.html to handle word wrapping appropriately for different content types\n\n**Auth System Enhancements:**\n- Implemented `Delete()` method in AuthService with cascading deletion of revoked user records\n  - Only root user can delete\n  - Only revoked users can be deleted\n  - Cascades to all descendants (users issued by the deleted user)\n  - Returns affected usernames for audit trail\n- Added DELETE `/api/auth/users/{username}` endpoint with proper authorization checks\n- Extended `/api/auth/me` and `/api/auth/users` endpoints to include `isRoot` flag\n- Added delete button in tokens.html UI (visible only to root user) with confirmation dialog\n\n**Testing:**\n- Added comprehensive test case `Delete_OnlyRoot_OnlyRevoked_CascadesAndRemoves()` covering all delete scenarios and edge cases\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Domain history is strictly client-side and never sent to the server\n- Navigation now consistently shows the current page as non-clickable text while other pages remain as links\n- Delete operations provide user feedback showing which records were removed\n- Auth state properly distinguishes between root user and admin users for permission checks\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01GD91V9CQm9JxmKWJbpm2tC",
